---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
---

<Layout title="Chapters">
  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">Chapters Overview</Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        Dive into <strong>Kubernetes Recipes</strong>, a comprehensive and practical guide for mastering container orchestration. Each chapter addresses real-world scenarios, offering hands-on solutions and best practices.
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 space-y-6 text-slate-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 1: Getting Started</strong><br />
        Learn how to set up Kubernetes environments using tools like Minikube, k3s, and kubeadm. A foundational guide to cluster setup and basic operations.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 2: Configuring Stateless Applications</strong><br />
        Covers namespaces, pods, environment variables, multi-container setups, secrets, and configuration strategies for non-persistent workloads.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 3: Configuring Stateful Applications</strong><br />
        Focuses on databases, data persistence, migrations, SDLC best practices, and handling complex workloads.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 4: Kubernetes on Cloud Providers</strong><br />
        Step-by-step deployment on GKE, AKS, EKS, and other providers, plus tools like Kubespray and Sonobuoy for conformance testing.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 5: Developer Experience in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        Enhance your development workflow using tools like Lens, DevSpace, and VS Code integrated with Kubernetes.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 6: Scaling and Resiliency</strong><br />
        Techniques for autoscaling (HPA, VPA, KEDA), resource optimization, and deployment strategies using Karpenter and vCluster.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 7: Storage in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        Explore static/dynamic provisioning, NFS, persistent disks across cloud platforms, and custom StorageClasses.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 8: Networking in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        In-depth discussion on service types, traffic routing, Istio, network policies, and troubleshooting.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 9: Performance Observability in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        Learn observability tools including Prometheus, Grafana, ELK, Fluentd, OpenTelemetry, and Cloud-specific monitors.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 10: Control Plane Administration and Package Management</strong><br />
        Administration of core components (kubelet, scheduler, etc.), node operations, upgrades, and using Helm for packages.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 11: Security in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        Covers secrets management, RBAC, PodSecurity, AppArmor, Seccomp, and securing clusters with Istio.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 12: Emerging and Advanced Kubernetes Concepts</strong><br />
        Looks at FaaS, WebAssembly, HPC, CRDs, and deploying AI/ML workloads, including MLOps and air-gapped DevOps.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 13: Best Practices in Kubernetes</strong><br />
        Offers practical advice on resource limits, health checks, namespaces, multi-tenancy, and immutable infrastructure.
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Chapter 14: Additional Kubernetes Resources</strong><br />
        Highlights CNCF resources, community involvement, sustainability, KubeCon, and tools like Kepler.
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
